                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <p>Deeply incised letters with a regular module (although with a little bit of cramping in lines 2 and 3) and of even height throughout. Terminal serifs of a simple wedge form. Alpha is consistently pronounced broken bar; epsilon has shorter middle bar, only lightly connected, with slight overlap of the top and bottom bar; theta is a full circle, with a short detached mid-stroke; kappa has shorter arms (especially the lower arm); mu has vertical outer strokes, with the middle strokes extending three-quarters of the way down to the base line; omicron is full size; pi has slightly overlapping crossbar, with equal length verticals; rho a large rounded eye; sigma has parallel top and bottom strokes, with a slight extension at the join of the mid-strokes; phi has small eye with slightly extended vertical; omega is slightly smaller than the other letters, tear-drop shaped, joined to the base line (but the eye does not close before the baseline) </p>
